{
  "texts": [
    "While this model represents a state-of-the-art approach to reasoningenhanced LLMs, the findings may not be generalizable to all LLMs, especially those with different architectures or training methodologies.",
    "Third, the expert validation is still subject to the inherent limitations of human judgment and potential biases.",
    "Another limitation is that we only had a single medical expert evaluate the medical reasoning of the model.",
    "Building on the reasoning failures identified in this study, we outline six targeted avenues to improve the clinical robustness of large language models (LLMs).",
    "Extending the work by Wu et al. (2025) on creating highquality, explanation-rich datasets of medical reasoning, we advocate assembling collections with chain-of-thought medical reasoning."
  ]
}